about.long_description:
Terra Firma specializes in Landscape Architecture and Planning consultancy services. Since its inception in 1985, the firm has successfully designed and executed landscape projects of varying scale from residential landscapes to regional parks.

Our work ethos is defined by a strong passion for design and innovation along with a responsible stance on environmental sensibilities.

We are a small yet dynamic cohort of talented professionals led by by Mr. Rohit Marol with a wealth of experience in delivering projects from concept to execution across typologies.

home.short_description:
THE TERRA FIRMA STORY

‘Terra Firma’ which was not quite what it was called way back in the mid 80’s was started as an experiment to pursue something ‘different’ from architecture by young Rohit Marol who returned to Bangalore after completing his Master’s Degree in Landscape Architecture from School of Planning & Architecture, New Delhi. Looking for opportunities in landscape architecture, a profession barely recognized and in a rather nascent state at the time, Rohit realised there were not too many. What began as a journey of self exploration eventually metamorphosed into ‘Terra Firma’ a firm committed to designing landscapes with deep rooted commitment to environmental and cultural sensibilities.

The early years were about learning and executing turnkey projects and educating clients on the role of landscape architecture and Rohit’s own passion and self discovery as a landscape architect.

Three decades later, the firm remains committed to meeting clients’ aspirations, taking up new challenges and bringing a unique identity to every project apart from fulfilling aesthetic and functional needs. We place emphasis on the ‘experiential” perspective in landscape design. Through design we passionately aspire to engage the user or target group in a landscape experience that one can enjoy, draw inspiration from or simply connect to Nature.

Thirty years later, Terra Firma under the continued mentorship of Rohit Marol, has a multi- disciplinary team of thirty plus employees working from offices at Bangalore & Chennai to deliver landscape projects that bring the community together and create unique spaces to live, work, and play.

-KeVKWHsM-XQk92PRF7n.description: We encourage landscape architects and architects with a passion for landscape design backed by strong design skills to join our team at Bangalore or Chennai.
-KeVKWHsM-XQk92PRF7n.name: Landscape Architects
-KeVKWHsM-XQk92PRF7n.requirements:
Master's Degree in Landscape Architecture or Bachelor's Degree in Architecture from a recognized institution.

A minimum of 2 to 7 years experience in deisgn and delivery of landscape projects. Graduate architects with exposure to landscape architetcure may also apply.

Should be able to conceptualise, understand and produce landscape drawings and documentation relating to concept presentation, design development and detailed working drawings under the guidance of senior landscape architects.

Good working knowledge and speed in Autocad versions 2012 and above is a must.

A reasonable level of skill and ability to demonstrate and present deisgn intent through hand sketches and / or illustrative software tools such as Google Sketch Up. Photoshop, 3DS Max etc; will be an added advantage.

Should have sound knowledge of details and materials related to landscape design and construction.

The firm encourages and will suitable reward the contributions of the candidate for the above skill set.

Interested candidates may mail their updated resume and portfolio with the following details

Present CTC,

Expected CTC,

Joining time

.

-KehNhXrdltdKuQOBHT9.description: Situated on a dying lake bed, the key intervention through landscape design was to rejuvenate part of the lake and to provide a large lung space for the city. This green space would also be instrumental in attracting avifauna back to the city and provide it with a safe environs within urban limits.
-KehNhXrdltdKuQOBHT9.name: JP Park

-KehPRzU0WsgxPdKow-d.description: Aparna sarovar is a high-end residential development located close to the IT hub of Hyderabd. The open spaces are conceptualised based on the elements of Nature : Earth, Water, Fire, Wind and Sky. These themes were interpreted using contemporary materials and spatial configurations and accentuated through planting.
-KehPRzU0WsgxPdKow-d.name: Aparna Sarovar

-KehdvP13ZE17vryYB26.description: Vista Do Mar is an exclusive 13 acre sea-front residential development set in a picture perfect location blessed with stunning views of the Arabian Sea and the Goan coastline. The landscape is an interplay of warm tropical colours and cool ocean vistas. The landscaped spaces were designed to provide a sense of privacy while preserving the drama of open vistas and panoramic views. The meditation deck and infinity pool located atop the site complement and accentuate the sea-side setting.
-KehdvP13ZE17vryYB26.name: Vista Do Mar

-KehfrQAxjmyZ9hXjsfE.description: Master Planned by HOK, USA, this 40 acre composite development has a large manmade lake that acts as an anchor integrating multiple land uses along its periphery. The lake and its fringes jave been designed as a contemporary urban public space. The shopping mall opens into a linear plaza terminating into an amphi-theatre with a boardwalk lining the lake. The office tower opens out into a curvilinear lakeside promenade punctuated by shade structures that intend to refresh and rejuvenate body and mind. The residential block spills out into a passive green overlooking the lake.
-KehfrQAxjmyZ9hXjsfE.name: Brigade  Gateway

-Kem1hb9cHyk7nbQG-R8.description: Designed within the constraints of a disused quarry, the landscape for Milroc Kadamba blends contemporary apartment lifestyles with the warmth and charm of old Goa. The earthy tones of natural laterite and luxuriant vegetation that renews itself every monsoon season create an urban retreat where one can delight in the sounds and sights of Nature.
-Kem1hb9cHyk7nbQG-R8.name: Milroc Kadamba

-KeqyAxBrVcdEykIhThb.description: The project was an opportunity to design outdoor spaces for an elite lifestyle catering to the client's various moods and activities. The generous four acre space allowed for the harmonious blend of wood, red sandstone, granite and basalt along with a thoughtfully designed planting palette.
-KeqyAxBrVcdEykIhThb.name: Bhatia Residences

-KeqyMiigxJ50CU491fy.description: A large suburban house on the outskirts of Bangalore where the landscape is designed as an urban retreat that rejuvenates body and soul. Man made elements complement the natural components of the site, instilling a sense of peace and harmony. The highlight of the project is a large interior water court with floating panels that act as a strong visual anchor from within the farm house.
-KeqyMiigxJ50CU491fy.name: Jawahar Farmhouse

-Keqz0EZ5gwr6rjUQVuZ.description: The design is a contemoprary expression using simple geometry and clean lines. The innovative use of stone, glass, wood and steel harmoniously integrated with each other creates a calm and soothing ambience.
-Keqz0EZ5gwr6rjUQVuZ.name: Shands Residence

-KeqzOQ6nvEQZ0cEbmDY.description: A farmhouse perched on the edge of a ridge overlooking a valley that reaches out to the sea was designed to provide for family gatherings and weekend relaxation. The design takes advantage of the natural topography of the site to capture and enhance the stunning vistas reaching out beyond the site.
-KeqzOQ6nvEQZ0cEbmDY.name: Quiet Retreat

-Keqzy7gJlLBKuoQVbd-.description: A large rain curtain heralds the entrance to the hotel, separating the porch from the surrounding development. On the fourth floor a terrace anchored by a large infinity pool complements the setting for outdoor banqueting and fine dining.
-Keqzy7gJlLBKuoQVbd-.name: Sheraton at Brigade Gateway

-Ker-7HcCReYLHDqXA25.description: An all-suite hotel with a large central atrium that serves as a reception, lounge and restaurant. The atrium is designed to bring about a feeling of an oasis through the use of gurgling fountains, clusters of palms, and natural materials. A pool with a fabric roof creates an ambience of intimacy and solitude.
-Ker-7HcCReYLHDqXA25.name: The Paul

-Ker1JL4kx3pK-WVnXrK.description: The design for this office buliding consisted of an atrium space that was required to be dynamic and in continuum of the nature of the user group, but also at the same time be a relaxation area. The space was designed to create a balance between technology and nature.
-Ker1JL4kx3pK-WVnXrK.name: DivyaSree Chambers

-Ker43S4YnFKI1YWhdhE.description: The focus of the landscape was a central atrium, which combined stainless steel, wood, stone and water to invoke a sense of peace and tranquilty in a busy work environment.
-Ker43S4YnFKI1YWhdhE.name: Maruti Infotech Centre.

-KerjSQhA3bSpD6pIa90.description:
The entry water feature draws inspiration from the traditional 'kudams' or 'water pots’ set in a composition against a gabion backdrop exuding a sense of peace and tranquillity.
The illuminated planters alongside the pool deck add a sculptural fee to the poolside.
The spaces are accentuated through lush tropical planting combining a variety of forms, colours and textures
-KerjSQhA3bSpD6pIa90.name: Marriott at Kochi Airport

-KerlmTWoplkZ4tusClq.description: The highlight of the design is the infinity pool set against the background of the Mullayanagiri Hills (the highest peak of the Western Ghats in Karnataka) in a conscious attempt to integrate the designed landscape and the breathtaking beauty of the natural landscape beyond.
-KerlmTWoplkZ4tusClq.name: Trivik

-KfGjLfMaoDnGB7TX4TI.description: The landscape links three linear apartment blocks through a series of terraces making imaginative use of the steeply sloping site. The terraces provide spaces for various activities such as the pool, congregation spaces, plazas and play areas. Contemporary feature elements merge seamlessly with lush tropical planting.
-KfGjLfMaoDnGB7TX4TI.name: Prudential Paradise
